     1→---
     2→name: cairo-contracts
     3→description: Use when writing Cairo smart contracts on Starknet — contract structure, storage, events, interfaces, components, OpenZeppelin v3 patterns, and common contract templates.
     4→license: Apache-2.0
     5→metadata: {"author":"starknet-agentic","version":"1.0.0","org":"keep-starknet-strange"}
     6→keywords: [cairo, contracts, starknet, openzeppelin, components, storage, events, interfaces, erc20, erc721]
     7→allowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Write, Glob, Grep, Task]
     8→user-invocable: true
     9→---
    10→
    11→# Cairo Contracts
    12→
    13→Reference for writing Cairo smart contracts on Starknet. Covers structure, storage, events, interfaces, components, and OpenZeppelin v3 patterns.
    14→
    15→> **Optimization:** After your contract compiles and tests pass, use the [cairo-optimization](../cairo-optimization/) skill as a separate pass.
    16→
    17→## When to Use
    18→
    19→- Writing a new Starknet smart contract from scratch
    20→- Adding storage, events, or interfaces to an existing contract
    21→- Using OpenZeppelin components (Ownable, ERC20, ERC721, AccessControl, Upgradeable)
    22→- Implementing the component pattern with `embeddable_as`
    23→- Structuring a multi-contract project with Scarb
    24→
    25→**Not for:** Gas optimization (use cairo-optimization), testing (use cairo-testing), deployment (use cairo-deploy)
    26→
    27→## Contract Structure
    28→
    29→Every Starknet contract follows this skeleton:
    30→
    31→```cairo
    32→#[starknet::contract]
    33→mod MyContract {
    34→    use starknet::ContractAddress;
    35→    use starknet::storage::{StoragePointerReadAccess, StoragePointerWriteAccess};
    36→
    37→    #[storage]
    38→    struct Storage {
    39→        owner: ContractAddress,
    40→        balance: u256,
    41→    }
    42→
    43→    #[event]
    44→    #[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
    45→    enum Event {
    46→        Transfer: Transfer,
    47→    }
    48→
    49→    #[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
    50→    struct Transfer {
    51→        #[key]
    52→        from: ContractAddress,
    53→        #[key]
    54→        to: ContractAddress,
    55→        amount: u256,
    56→    }
    57→
    58→    #[constructor]
    59→    fn constructor(ref self: ContractState, owner: ContractAddress) {
    60→        self.owner.write(owner);
    61→    }
    62→
    63→    #[abi(embed_v0)]
    64→    impl MyContractImpl of super::IMyContract<ContractState> {
    65→        fn get_balance(self: @ContractState) -> u256 {
    66→            self.balance.read()
    67→        }
    68→
    69→        fn transfer(ref self: ContractState, to: ContractAddress, amount: u256) {
    70→            // implementation
    71→        }
    72→    }
    73→}
    74→```
    75→
    76→## Interfaces
    77→
    78→Define interfaces outside the contract module. Use `#[starknet::interface]`:
    79→
    80→```cairo
    81→#[starknet::interface]
    82→trait IMyContract<TContractState> {
    83→    fn get_balance(self: @TContractState) -> u256;
    84→    fn transfer(ref self: TContractState, to: ContractAddress, amount: u256);
    85→}
    86→```
    87→
    88→- `self: @TContractState` — read-only (view function)
    89→- `ref self: TContractState` — read-write (external function)
    90→
    91→## Storage
    92→
    93→### Basic Types
    94→
    95→```cairo
    96→#[storage]
    97→struct Storage {
    98→    value: felt252,           // single felt
    99→    counter: u128,            // unsigned integer
   100→    owner: ContractAddress,   // address
   101→    is_active: bool,          // boolean
   102→}
   103→```
   104→
   105→### Maps
   106→
   107→```cairo
   108→use starknet::storage::Map;
   109→
   110→#[storage]
   111→struct Storage {
   112→    balances: Map<ContractAddress, u256>,
   113→    allowances: Map<(ContractAddress, ContractAddress), u256>,
   114→}
   115→
   116→// Usage:
   117→fn get_balance(self: @ContractState, account: ContractAddress) -> u256 {
   118→    self.balances.read(account)
   119→}
   120→
   121→fn set_allowance(ref self: ContractState, owner: ContractAddress, spender: ContractAddress, amount: u256) {
   122→    self.allowances.write((owner, spender), amount);
   123→}
   124→```
   125→
   126→### Composite Key Maps (Nested Map Alternative)
   127→
   128→Prefer composite key tuples over nested Maps:
   129→
   130→```cairo
   131→use starknet::storage::Map;
   132→
   133→#[storage]
   134→struct Storage {
   135→    // Map<(owner, spender), amount> — preferred over nested Map
   136→    allowances: Map<(ContractAddress, ContractAddress), u256>,
   137→}
   138→
   139→// Usage:
   140→let amount = self.allowances.entry((owner, spender)).read();
   141→self.allowances.entry((owner, spender)).write(new_amount);
   142→```
   143→
   144→## Events
   145→
   146→```cairo
   147→#[event]
   148→#[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
   149→enum Event {
   150→    Transfer: Transfer,
   151→    Approval: Approval,
   152→}
   153→
   154→#[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
   155→struct Transfer {
   156→    #[key]    // indexed — used for filtering
   157→    from: ContractAddress,
   158→    #[key]
   159→    to: ContractAddress,
   160→    amount: u256,  // not indexed — stored in data
   161→}
   162→
   163→// Emit:
   164→self.emit(Transfer { from, to, amount });
   165→```
   166→
   167→## Components (OpenZeppelin v3 Pattern)
   168→
   169→Components are reusable contract modules. This is the standard pattern in Cairo / OZ v3:
   170→
   171→### Using a Component
   172→
   173→The **Mixin pattern** is the most common approach in OZ v3 — it exposes all standard interface methods (e.g., `balance_of`, `transfer`, `approve`) in a single `impl` block:
   174→
   175→```cairo
   176→#[starknet::contract]
   177→mod MyToken {
   178→    use openzeppelin_access::ownable::OwnableComponent;
   179→    use openzeppelin_token::erc20::{ERC20Component, ERC20HooksEmptyImpl};
   180→
   181→    component!(path: OwnableComponent, storage: ownable, event: OwnableEvent);
   182→    component!(path: ERC20Component, storage: erc20, event: ERC20Event);
   183→
   184→    // Embed external implementations (makes functions callable from outside)
   185→    #[abi(embed_v0)]
   186→    impl OwnableMixinImpl = OwnableComponent::OwnableMixinImpl<ContractState>;
   187→    #[abi(embed_v0)]
   188→    impl ERC20MixinImpl = ERC20Component::ERC20MixinImpl<ContractState>;
   189→
   190→    // Internal implementations (for use inside the contract)
   191→    impl OwnableInternalImpl = OwnableComponent::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   192→    impl ERC20InternalImpl = ERC20Component::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   193→
   194→    #[storage]
   195→    struct Storage {
   196→        #[substorage(v0)]
   197→        ownable: OwnableComponent::Storage,
   198→        #[substorage(v0)]
   199→        erc20: ERC20Component::Storage,
   200→    }
   201→
   202→    #[event]
   203→    #[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
   204→    enum Event {
   205→        #[flat]
   206→        OwnableEvent: OwnableComponent::Event,
   207→        #[flat]
   208→        ERC20Event: ERC20Component::Event,
   209→    }
   210→
   211→    #[constructor]
   212→    fn constructor(ref self: ContractState, owner: ContractAddress) {
   213→        self.ownable.initializer(owner);
   214→        self.erc20.initializer("MyToken", "MTK");
   215→    }
   216→}
   217→```
   218→
   219→### Writing a Component
   220→
   221→```cairo
   222→#[starknet::component]
   223→mod MyComponent {
   224→    use starknet::ContractAddress;
   225→    use starknet::storage::{StoragePointerReadAccess, StoragePointerWriteAccess};
   226→
   227→    #[storage]
   228→    struct Storage {
   229→        value: u256,
   230→    }
   231→
   232→    #[event]
   233→    #[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
   234→    enum Event {
   235→        ValueChanged: ValueChanged,
   236→    }
   237→
   238→    #[derive(Drop, starknet::Event)]
   239→    struct ValueChanged {
   240→        new_value: u256,
   241→    }
   242→
   243→    #[embeddable_as(MyComponentImpl)]
   244→    impl MyComponent<
   245→        TContractState, +HasComponent<TContractState>
   246→    > of super::IMyComponent<ComponentState<TContractState>> {
   247→        fn get_value(self: @ComponentState<TContractState>) -> u256 {
   248→            self.value.read()
   249→        }
   250→
   251→        fn set_value(ref self: ComponentState<TContractState>, new_value: u256) {
   252→            self.value.write(new_value);
   253→            self.emit(ValueChanged { new_value });
   254→        }
   255→    }
   256→}
   257→```
   258→
   259→## Common OpenZeppelin Components
   260→
   261→### Scarb.toml Dependencies
   262→
   263→```toml
   264→[dependencies]
   265→starknet = ">=2.12.0"
   266→openzeppelin_access = "3.0.0"
   267→openzeppelin_token = "3.0.0"
   268→openzeppelin_upgrades = "3.0.0"
   269→openzeppelin_introspection = "3.0.0"
   270→openzeppelin_security = "3.0.0"
   271→```
   272→
   273→> **Note:** OZ packages are on the [Scarb registry](https://scarbs.dev). No git tags needed. Check `scarbs.dev` for the latest version.
   274→
   275→### Ownable
   276→
   277→```cairo
   278→use openzeppelin_access::ownable::OwnableComponent;
   279→
   280→component!(path: OwnableComponent, storage: ownable, event: OwnableEvent);
   281→
   282→#[abi(embed_v0)]
   283→impl OwnableMixinImpl = OwnableComponent::OwnableMixinImpl<ContractState>;
   284→impl OwnableInternalImpl = OwnableComponent::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   285→
   286→// In constructor:
   287→self.ownable.initializer(owner);
   288→
   289→// In functions:
   290→self.ownable.assert_only_owner();
   291→```
   292→
   293→### Upgradeable
   294→
   295→```cairo
   296→use openzeppelin_upgrades::UpgradeableComponent;
   297→use openzeppelin_upgrades::interface::IUpgradeable;
   298→
   299→component!(path: UpgradeableComponent, storage: upgradeable, event: UpgradeableEvent);
   300→
   301→impl UpgradeableInternalImpl = UpgradeableComponent::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   302→
   303→#[abi(embed_v0)]
   304→impl UpgradeableImpl of IUpgradeable<ContractState> {
   305→    fn upgrade(ref self: ContractState, new_class_hash: ClassHash) {
   306→        self.ownable.assert_only_owner();
   307→        self.upgradeable.upgrade(new_class_hash);
   308→    }
   309→}
   310→```
   311→
   312→### ERC20
   313→
   314→```cairo
   315→use openzeppelin_token::erc20::{ERC20Component, ERC20HooksEmptyImpl};
   316→
   317→component!(path: ERC20Component, storage: erc20, event: ERC20Event);
   318→
   319→#[abi(embed_v0)]
   320→impl ERC20MixinImpl = ERC20Component::ERC20MixinImpl<ContractState>;
   321→impl ERC20InternalImpl = ERC20Component::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   322→
   323→// In constructor:
   324→self.erc20.initializer("TokenName", "TKN");
   325→self.erc20.mint(recipient, initial_supply);
   326→```
   327→
   328→### AccessControl
   329→
   330→```cairo
   331→use openzeppelin_access::accesscontrol::AccessControlComponent;
   332→use openzeppelin_access::accesscontrol::DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE;
   333→
   334→component!(path: AccessControlComponent, storage: access_control, event: AccessControlEvent);
   335→
   336→#[abi(embed_v0)]
   337→impl AccessControlMixinImpl = AccessControlComponent::AccessControlMixinImpl<ContractState>;
   338→impl AccessControlInternalImpl = AccessControlComponent::InternalImpl<ContractState>;
   339→
   340→const MINTER_ROLE: felt252 = selector!("MINTER_ROLE");
   341→
   342→// In constructor:
   343→self.access_control.initializer();
   344→self.access_control._grant_role(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, admin);
   345→self.access_control._grant_role(MINTER_ROLE, minter);
   346→
   347→// In functions:
   348→self.access_control.assert_only_role(MINTER_ROLE);
   349→```
   350→
   351→## Project Structure
   352→
   353→```
   354→my-project/
   355→  Scarb.toml
   356→  src/
   357→    lib.cairo          # mod declarations
   358→    contract.cairo     # main contract
   359→    interfaces.cairo   # trait definitions
   360→    components/
   361→      mod.cairo
   362→      my_component.cairo
   363→  tests/
   364→    test_contract.cairo
   365→```
   366→
   367→### lib.cairo
   368→
   369→```cairo
   370→mod contract;
   371→mod interfaces;
   372→mod components;
   373→```
   374→
   375→## Common Patterns
   376→
   377→### Reentrancy Guard
   378→
   379→```cairo
   380→#[storage]
   381→struct Storage {
   382→    entered: bool,
   383→}
   384→
   385→fn _enter(ref self: ContractState) {
   386→    assert(!self.entered.read(), 'ReentrancyGuard: reentrant');
   387→    self.entered.write(true);
   388→}
   389→
   390→fn _exit(ref self: ContractState) {
   391→    self.entered.write(false);
   392→}
   393→```
   394→
   395→### Pausable
   396→
   397→```cairo
   398→use openzeppelin_security::pausable::PausableComponent;
   399→
   400→component!(path: PausableComponent, storage: pausable, event: PausableEvent);
   401→
   402→// In functions:
   403→self.pausable.assert_not_paused();
   404→```
   405→
   406→### Constructor Validation
   407→
   408→```cairo
   409→#[constructor]
   410→fn constructor(ref self: ContractState, owner: ContractAddress) {
   411→    assert(!owner.is_zero(), 'Owner cannot be zero');
   412→    self.ownable.initializer(owner);
   413→}
   414→```
   415→

